# Page-Specific JavaScript

This directory contains page-specific JavaScript files.

## Structure:
Place your page-specific JavaScript here when needed.

## Example:
```
pages/
├── welcome.js
├── about.js
└── contact.js
```

## Usage:
Import page-specific JavaScript in your Blade templates:

```blade
@vite(['resources/js/laravel/pages/welcome.js'])
```

Or import in home.js if needed globally:

```javascript
import './laravel/pages/welcome';
```

## Best Practices:
- Keep page-specific code isolated
- Use Alpine.js components for reusable functionality
- Only create page-specific files when necessary
- Document dependencies and purpose
